OL,7,FIvers, now 22 and formerly of Minster-
OL,8,Fon-Sea, was not charged in relation to
OL,9,Fthe collision itself, but was charged
OL,10,Fwith dangerous driving and perverting
OL,11,Fthe course of justice after the
OL,12,Fcollision.
OL,14,FHe was also charged with two counts of
OL,15,Fdangerous driving in relation to the
OL,16,Ffootage found on his phone.
OL,18,FHe pleaded guilty to those charges and
OL,19,Fwas jailed for one year and three
OL,20,Fmonths.
